description: The NexSens TS110 Temperature String measures water temperature by incorporating multiple sensors into a single 3-conductor cable, suspended vertically in a water column. This capability provides high precision, multi-point temperature profiling for environmental applications. The TS110 is designed for harsh environments and is submersible up to 200 m in fresh, brackish, or seawater. When connected to the NexSens iSIC data logger and iChart software, the instrument is truly plug-and-play. No programming is required! It is typically used in one of the following configurations: standalone data logger, direct-connect to PC, bottom-deployed, or surface buoy.
